{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":7025,"record_hash":"sha256:23a2113d819ec26df5921784444e05724ff562ea4af0afea73a47ec37db05aa0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:30:23.674Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: [REDACTED:entropy].md\n@@\n ## Review Passes\n \n Run these as separate passes. Preserve behavior unless a specific bug is found.\n@@\n Do not ask for a broad rewrite. The output should be small findings, not a new\n architecture.\n+\n+## Cleanup Recipe\n+\n+Use this procedure when doing a maintainability cleanup pass on\n+`crates/but-agentlog`.\n+\n+### Step 0. Establish The Baseline\n+\n+Run the narrow checks before changing code:\n+\n+```text\n+cargo fmt --check\n+cargo test -p but-agentlog\n+cargo check -p but --features agentlog\n+cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps\n+```\n+\n+If the baseline is already broken, fix or document that separately before\n+starting cleanup. A cleanup pass should not hide pre-existing failures.\n+\n+### Step 1. Main Agent Reads The Code\n+\n+The main agent should read the crate itself first:\n+\n+- `src/lib.rs`\n+- `src/cli.rs`\n+- `src/capture.rs`\n+- `src/transcript.rs`\n+- `src/gitmeta.rs`\n+- `src/redaction.rs`\n+- nearby tests\n+\n+Do not spawn subagents yet. The main agent needs enough context to judge whether\n+subagent feedback is useful or just generic.\n+\n+### Step 2. Spawn Focused Review Subagents\n+\n+Use subagents for independent review, not implementation, at this stage. Give\n+each subagent a narrow lens and ask for findings only.\n+\n+Recommended subagents:\n+\n+- **Deletion reviewer**: find fake extensibility, one-use helpers, dead fields,\n+  ceremonial modules, and comments that repeat code.\n+- **Boundary reviewer**: check that CLI, capture orchestration, transcript\n+  parsing, GitMeta writing, and redaction stay separated.\n+- **Rust reviewer**: check visibility, error boundaries, ownership/cloning,\n+  naming, and idiomatic Rust.\n+- **Test reviewer**: check whether tests protect behavior and whether any tests\n+  are brittle implementation mirrors.\n+\n+Optional subagents:\n+\n+- **Security/privacy reviewer**, when redaction or transcript storage changed.\n+- **Performance reviewer**, when parsing, redaction, or GitMeta read/write loops\n+  changed.\n+\n+Do not ask subagents to rewrite files. Their output should be a short list of\n+high-signal findings with file/line references when possible.\n+\n+### Step 3. Triage Findings\n+\n+The main agent should merge subagent feedback into three buckets:\n+\n+- **Fix now**: behavior risk, privacy risk, confusing boundary, or easy\n+  simplification.\n+- **Document only**: useful future concern but not POC-sized.\n+- **Ignore**: speculative architecture, taste-only renames, or changes that make\n+  the POC larger.\n+\n+Prefer deleting or renaming over introducing new abstractions. If a finding\n+requires a new framework, it is probably not a cleanup finding.\n+\n+### Step 4. Make Small Behavior-Preserving Edits\n+\n+Edit in small groups:\n+\n+1. deletion/inlining\n+2. naming\n+3. visibility tightening\n+4. comment cleanup\n+5. test cleanup\n+\n+Run `cargo fmt` after edits. Avoid mixing a behavior fix with broad cleanup\n+unless the behavior fix is tiny and directly discovered by the cleanup.\n+\n+### Step 5. Run Verification\n+\n+Run:\n+\n+```text\n+cargo fmt --check\n+cargo test -p but-agentlog\n+cargo check -p but --features agentlog\n+cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps\n+cargo machete\n+```\n+\n+If dependencies did not change, `cargo machete` is still cheap and catches\n+cleanup leftovers.\n+\n+### Step 6. Optional Second Review\n+\n+After edits, spawn one or two fresh subagents only if the diff is non-trivial.\n+\n+Good second-pass prompts:\n+\n+- \"Review only the cleanup diff. Did behavior accidentally change?\"\n+- \"Look for new complexity introduced by the cleanup.\"\n+- \"Check whether any tests became weaker or more implementation-coupled.\"\n+\n+Avoid repeating the full four-subagent review unless the cleanup touched many\n+modules. Re-review has diminishing returns.\n+\n+### Step 7. Summarize The Result\n+\n+The final summary should say:\n+\n+- what was removed or clarified\n+- whether behavior changed\n+- what validation ran\n+- any remaining deliberate POC tradeoffs\n+\n+Do not claim the crate is now \"future-proof.\" The point is that it is easier to\n+change later because it is smaller and clearer now.\n \n ## Cursor Note\n \n Do not force Cursor into the current JSONL parser path. Cursor's normal chat\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:30:23.674Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}